BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EsHj6Ps5ZEnFAR-l2Z0Xu
SUMMARY:Membership Luncheon - AI in Action
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260205T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description  This luncheon explores how AI is actively reshapin
	g small business operations\, marketing\, and workforce efficiency-and why
	 waiting to adapt is no longer a safe option. AI is already changing how c
	ustomers find you\, how fast you operate\, how you hire\, and how you comp
	ete. Businesses that understand this shift early are gaining visibility\, 
	saving time\, and increasing profitability. Those that don't are quietly f
	alling behind. At this luncheon\, attendees will: Experience live demonstr
	ations from industry experts: Rudi Alcott of FlareAI\, Nick Redick of AUC1
	 Consulting\, and DeiMarlon Scisney of The Data Guys Understand how AI imp
	acts marketing\, customer engagement\, and online visibility Explore how w
	orkforce efficiency is changing and what that means for hiring and product
	ivity Connect with peers who are navigating the same shifts and opportunit
	ies Walk away with insights you can act on immediately\, not theory This i
	s not a tech talk for experts. It's a relevance briefing for business owne
	rs who want to stay competitive in a rapidly changing economy. "Artificial
	 intelligence is not a substitute for human intelligence\; it is a tool to
	 amplify human creativity and ingenuity." - Satya Nadella\, CEO of Microso
	ft AI is no longer a future conversation. It's a business survival convers
	ation. If you're not in the room\, you're already behind the curve.\n\nFro
	m SEAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/membership-luncheon-ai-in
	-action/17982338/2026-02-05T00
LOCATION:Green River College - Kent Campus\, 417 Ramsay Way\, Suite 112\, R
	oom 282/283\, Kent\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
